1
00:02:39,771 --> 00:02:41,313
Heil fucking Hitler.

2
00:03:05,980 --> 00:03:09,355
Ladies, they're lighting fireworks for us.

3
00:03:09,438 --> 00:03:12,480
- Have a good one, girls.
- See ya in the morning, comrades.

4
00:03:12,563 --> 00:03:14,146
- God willing.
- Evening, love.

5
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:15,480
All right, Sid?

6
00:03:28,396 --> 00:03:30,813
Make us a cup of tea, darling, will you?

7
00:03:30,896 --> 00:03:32,855
{\an8}- Where you been?
- Evening, all.

8
00:03:32,938 --> 00:03:34,980
{\an8}Come sit down.
We've saved a space for you.

9
00:03:35,063 --> 00:03:37,063
{\an8}Okay, ladies. Agnes is here.

10
00:03:38,605 --> 00:03:40,730
{\an8}Hi.

11
00:03:40,813 --> 00:03:44,480
{\an8}<i>Happy birthday to you </i>

12
00:03:44,563 --> 00:03:45,563
{\an8}Join in.

13
00:03:45,646 --> 00:03:48,355
{\an8}<i>Happy birthday to you </i>

14
00:03:48,438 --> 00:03:49,521
{\an8}Look at this.

15
00:03:50,396 --> 00:03:54,480
{\an8}<i>- Happy birthday, dear Agnes</i>
- What a beauty.

16
00:03:54,563 --> 00:03:55,896
Thanks, everybody.

17
00:03:55,980 --> 00:04:00,605
<i>Happy birthday to you </i>

18
00:05:39,313 --> 00:05:41,938
Did you see the glow
over the hills last night, Tom?

19
00:05:43,646 --> 00:05:45,271
Birmingham caught hell.

20
00:05:47,771 --> 00:05:49,563
They've hit Small Heath, Tom.

21
00:05:51,980 --> 00:05:53,188
Your home.

22
00:05:56,188 --> 00:05:57,313
Sick.

23
00:05:58,521 --> 00:06:01,021
Last night,
a Gypsy family escaping the bombs

24
00:06:01,105 --> 00:06:03,396
has cut through the fence
and got onto the land.

25
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,646
So move 'em on.

26
00:06:04,730 --> 00:06:06,396
They're Palmer family, Tommy.

27
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:09,896
Famous witches, fortune-tellers,
palm readers.

28
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:13,396
I want no one near this house.
Not even interesting people.

29
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,271
What I mean is, if I throw them off,

30
00:06:15,355 --> 00:06:17,605
I wouldn't want
one of them to curse me, Tom.

31
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:22,563
You're already cursed, my friend.

32
00:06:23,521 --> 00:06:26,855
Cursed to be the last man on Earth
who works for me.

33
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:32,855
When I was up there,

34
00:06:34,146 --> 00:06:37,396
one of the Palmer women
recognized me from the old days.

35
00:06:38,730 --> 00:06:41,438
She asked me if I knew
whatever happened to Tommy Shelby.

36
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:47,813
The lady called you the <i>Rom Baro</i>,
the king of all the Gypsies.

37
00:06:48,563 --> 00:06:50,063
Some king I was.

38
00:06:50,146 --> 00:06:53,438
Some king you still are, Tom,
to the Gypsies.

39
00:06:55,021 --> 00:06:56,521
What did you say to her?

40
00:06:56,605 --> 00:07:01,438
I said, "As far as I am aware,
the famous gangster Tommy Shelby

41
00:07:01,938 --> 00:07:03,855
has withdrawn from this world."

42
00:07:04,563 --> 00:07:06,355
"And he is writing a book."

43
00:07:33,605 --> 00:07:34,771
Fuck off.

44
00:08:10,771 --> 00:08:13,021
"<i>I'm not alone when I'm alone."</i>

45
00:08:21,313 --> 00:08:23,521
<i>"Spirits show themselves to me."</i>

46
00:08:27,063 --> 00:08:30,021
<i>"My dead daughter,</i>
<i>Ruby, plays in the garden."</i>

47
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:35,063
<i>"I found her scarf hanging from a branch…"</i>

48
00:08:37,938 --> 00:08:39,813
<i>"…where there was no scarf before."</i>

49
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,605
<i>"It could not have got there</i>
<i>any other way."</i>

50
00:08:46,730 --> 00:08:48,980
<i>"And now it sits here in front of me,</i>

51
00:08:50,313 --> 00:08:51,563
<i>on my desk."</i>

52
00:09:06,021 --> 00:09:07,688
I saw Ruby again.

53
00:09:21,521 --> 00:09:24,771
It'd be cowardly
to say it was all imagination.

54
00:09:27,021 --> 00:09:28,438
'Cause it isn't, Arthur.

55
00:09:30,563 --> 00:09:34,938
I'm many things, but I'm not a coward.

56
00:09:39,396 --> 00:09:41,730
Tom? You have a visitor.

57
00:09:42,813 --> 00:09:46,105
It's your sister.
She tried to call you from the phone box

58
00:09:46,188 --> 00:09:49,521
to tell you, no matter what you say,
she's coming to see you.

59
00:09:50,355 --> 00:09:52,230
She said she has bad news, Tom.

60
00:09:53,146 --> 00:09:55,646
She's at the gatehouse.
Will I… Will I go let her in?

61
00:09:58,105 --> 00:10:00,396
No. I'll go to her.

62
00:10:01,396 --> 00:10:04,021
Fuck's sakes, let her in, Tom.
It's your sister.

63
00:10:10,771 --> 00:10:11,771
Arthur.

64
00:10:28,896 --> 00:10:30,188
What bad news?

65
00:10:31,188 --> 00:10:34,521
Last night,
the BSA factory suffered a direct hit.

66
00:10:35,896 --> 00:10:39,230
All of the night shift
on the artillery depot were killed.

67
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:43,855
- You're their MP now.
- They don't need an MP.

68
00:10:43,938 --> 00:10:49,188
They pray to Christ and to you.
Neither one answers their prayers.

69
00:10:50,896 --> 00:10:52,688
I've got a war of me own, Ada.

70
00:10:56,021 --> 00:10:57,438
Inside of me head.

71
00:11:02,521 --> 00:11:05,730
You know, Tommy,
you have family who are not ghosts.

72
00:11:11,313 --> 00:11:13,563
How long since you spoke to your sons?

73
00:11:13,646 --> 00:11:15,396
I've been reviewing everything.

74
00:11:16,813 --> 00:11:18,021
Everything.

75
00:11:19,313 --> 00:11:21,188
I was never a father, Ada.

76
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,563
I was a form of government.

77
00:11:26,521 --> 00:11:29,230
I no longer believe
in government of any kind.

78
00:11:30,605 --> 00:11:32,021
I spoke to, uh…

79
00:11:33,438 --> 00:11:36,771
I spoke to Charles.
He's on the front line in North Africa.

80
00:11:38,563 --> 00:11:41,355
- Do you even listen to the radio?
- I don't have a radio.

81
00:11:42,521 --> 00:11:46,021
And your other son, your Gypsy son,

82
00:11:47,271 --> 00:11:51,313
is running the Peaky Blinders
like it's 1919 all over again.

83
00:11:52,688 --> 00:11:54,730
Worse than you and Arthur ever were.

84
00:11:55,480 --> 00:11:57,855
Then that is very bleak.

85
00:12:01,146 --> 00:12:03,063
Tommy, you've gotta come back with me.

86
00:12:04,355 --> 00:12:06,521
Speak some words
over the graves of the dead,

87
00:12:06,605 --> 00:12:10,021
and speak to your son
before he gets himself hung by the law

88
00:12:10,105 --> 00:12:12,063
or lynched by the people.

89
00:12:15,771 --> 00:12:16,771
Ada.

90
00:12:26,855 --> 00:12:28,355
I see things.

91
00:12:31,771 --> 00:12:33,355
Yeah, you always did.

92
00:12:35,438 --> 00:12:37,480
But since Arthur died…

93
00:12:37,563 --> 00:12:39,105
Since Arthur died…

94
00:12:44,188 --> 00:12:49,313
Since Arthur died, it's like a door
in me head has blown open.

95
00:12:49,980 --> 00:12:51,146
I can't close it.

96
00:13:20,605 --> 00:13:22,021
<i>Rub, dub</i>
<i>You just can't touch me</i>

97
00:13:22,105 --> 00:13:25,063
<i>Built like a boulder</i>
<i>And I'm rolling like I'm lovely</i>

98
00:13:25,146 --> 00:13:28,188
<i>You won't stop me</i>
<i>You won't shut me</i>

99
00:13:28,271 --> 00:13:31,230
<i>Something inside says</i>
<i>It's gonna get ugly</i>

100
00:13:31,313 --> 00:13:34,230
Boys, the Peaky Blinders are here.

101
00:13:35,855 --> 00:13:37,230
What shall we do?

102
00:13:37,938 --> 00:13:40,896
The Peaky Blinders are gonna do
whatever the Peaky Blinders want to do.

103
00:13:40,980 --> 00:13:44,563
<i>I'm a man</i>
<i>I am nobody's son</i>

104
00:13:54,646 --> 00:13:55,730
Right!

105
00:13:59,855 --> 00:14:01,355
That's it. Lovely.

106
00:14:03,063 --> 00:14:06,938
You've no right. You've no fucking right.

107
00:14:07,688 --> 00:14:10,438
The weapons in this armory
are bound for the front line.

108
00:14:11,730 --> 00:14:13,563
Are we gonna let them do this?!

109
00:14:14,188 --> 00:14:15,563
You should be arrested.

110
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:18,021
I don't care who the fuck you are.

111
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:31,438
We're the volunteer special constables,
registered this morning by my good friend

112
00:14:31,521 --> 00:14:34,855
the chief inspector
of the Birmingham police.

113
00:14:34,938 --> 00:14:36,480
That's who the fuck we are.

114
00:14:46,188 --> 00:14:48,355
Are you just gonna let them take
those weapons?

115
00:14:52,730 --> 00:14:55,980
Any man obstructing us
carrying out our lawful duty

116
00:14:56,563 --> 00:14:57,605
will be identified.

117
00:14:57,688 --> 00:15:01,438
Their home will be located,
and their families will be beaten.

118
00:15:02,646 --> 00:15:04,980
By order of the Peaky Blinders.

119
00:15:06,063 --> 00:15:08,771
By order of the Peaky Blinders.

120
00:15:15,271 --> 00:15:19,771
You Peaky Blinders
can scare the chief constable,

121
00:15:19,855 --> 00:15:21,313
but you don't scare me.

122
00:15:22,271 --> 00:15:25,605
I've seen worse in the last war
than you can imagine.

123
00:15:28,396 --> 00:15:29,938
You're a very brave man.

124
00:15:31,980 --> 00:15:33,188
Very brave.

125
00:15:36,646 --> 00:15:38,063
But very foolish.

126
00:15:44,855 --> 00:15:46,396
Stay down.

127
00:15:46,896 --> 00:15:48,563
Stay.

128
00:15:57,855 --> 00:15:59,521
Hey. Hey, hey. Hey.

129
00:15:59,605 --> 00:16:02,813
Shh. Hey, hey, hey. Hey.

130
00:16:03,855 --> 00:16:06,105
You fought your war in Flanders, old man.

131
00:16:08,021 --> 00:16:09,813
Don't fucking fight me.

132
00:16:18,396 --> 00:16:19,396
Right.

133
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:21,771
- Come on.
- Ready?

134
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,563
Told him.

135
00:16:28,188 --> 00:16:29,730
- Bastard!
- Hey.

136
00:16:29,813 --> 00:16:30,813
Yeah?

137
00:16:31,980 --> 00:16:36,271
Grab all the Stens, Brownings,
and all the dynamite you can carry.

138
00:16:36,771 --> 00:16:40,771
- And a nice new shiny pistol for me.
- What are you expecting, Duke?

139
00:16:43,896 --> 00:16:47,063
Trouble. Opportunity.

140
00:16:49,230 --> 00:16:50,230
Right.

141
00:16:50,855 --> 00:16:51,855
Come on.

142
00:16:59,521 --> 00:17:02,021
<i>German aircraft carried out</i>
<i>a swarm of attacks</i>

143
00:17:02,105 --> 00:17:03,688
<i>on Great Britain last night.</i>

144
00:17:03,771 --> 00:17:07,313
<i>The raids, which rampaged until dawn,</i>
<i>were scattered over the country.</i>

145
00:17:07,396 --> 00:17:08,563
Birmingham ablaze!

146
00:17:08,646 --> 00:17:11,146
<i>Enemy aircraft</i>
<i>have been reported on the south coast…</i>

147
00:17:11,230 --> 00:17:12,563
BSA factory hit!

148
00:17:12,646 --> 00:17:14,896
<i>…and the northwest,</i>
<i>as well as across the capital.</i>

149
00:17:15,938 --> 00:17:19,146
<i>Of the affected areas,</i>
<i>Birmingham was the worst hit,</i>

150
00:17:19,230 --> 00:17:21,271
<i>and it is almost impossible</i>
<i>to believe the fire…</i>

151
00:17:25,813 --> 00:17:28,438
The BSA's been roped off.

152
00:17:28,521 --> 00:17:31,355
But we can lay flowers,
talk to the relatives.

153
00:17:31,438 --> 00:17:35,271
- Okay.
- Mum. Come on.

154
00:17:35,896 --> 00:17:40,480
Well, they want Tommy, they get me.

155
00:17:57,438 --> 00:17:59,230
Just don't take it any further.

156
00:17:59,313 --> 00:18:02,271
You dare show your face, Ada Shelby.

157
00:18:02,813 --> 00:18:05,438
Your fucking Peaky Blinders did this.

158
00:18:17,480 --> 00:18:18,896
Out you get, boys.

159
00:18:19,646 --> 00:18:20,771
That's it.

160
00:18:26,313 --> 00:18:29,896
<i>A lot of people</i>
<i>Lot of people, lot of people </i>

161
00:18:29,980 --> 00:18:36,188
<i>Lot of people, lot of people</i>
<i>Like to be wise after the event</i>…

162
00:18:36,271 --> 00:18:37,271
Boysies.

163
00:18:37,355 --> 00:18:39,813
<i>Most in fact</i>
<i>Are wiser after time has passed</i>

164
00:18:39,896 --> 00:18:41,105
You all right, boys?

165
00:18:41,188 --> 00:18:45,230
<i>A lot of people</i>
<i>Like to be wise for a bet…</i>

166
00:18:46,063 --> 00:18:49,480
Duke, there's some fucker
from London. He's in the parlor.

167
00:18:50,146 --> 00:18:52,146
I told the kids to leave his car alone.

168
00:19:05,438 --> 00:19:06,646
Mr. Shelby.

169
00:19:10,271 --> 00:19:14,563
The ship will dock in Liverpool.

170
00:19:16,855 --> 00:19:17,855
Here.

171
00:19:18,438 --> 00:19:19,646
You can keep that.

172
00:19:21,521 --> 00:19:24,188
Freshly printed
counterfeit five-pound note.

173
00:19:25,146 --> 00:19:28,021
- There's plenty more where that came from.
- How much more?

174
00:19:29,063 --> 00:19:31,396
350 million pounds more.

175
00:19:32,646 --> 00:19:35,855
It's my job to introduce the money
into the British economy

176
00:19:35,938 --> 00:19:38,605
using organized criminal gangs.

177
00:19:38,688 --> 00:19:41,438
So Peaky Blinders gets a 20% cut.

178
00:19:41,521 --> 00:19:47,105
That's… 70 million pounds
to use as you see fit.

179
00:19:47,896 --> 00:19:51,396
But be ready
for the anarchy that comes after.

180
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:54,688
I'm ready. Yeah.

181
00:19:54,771 --> 00:20:01,230
Obviously, Berlin… would much prefer it
if I was talking to your father.

182
00:20:05,063 --> 00:20:06,105
Yeah?

183
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,771
Oh!

184
00:20:22,896 --> 00:20:24,438
I'm in charge now.

185
00:20:27,355 --> 00:20:29,521
Um… Duke?

186
00:20:29,605 --> 00:20:32,063
- Duke.
- Duke.

187
00:20:32,146 --> 00:20:33,730
Well, if you're in charge,

188
00:20:33,813 --> 00:20:38,188
I need to know that you are willing
to take part in an act of treason

189
00:20:38,271 --> 00:20:40,771
that will decide this war for Germany.

190
00:20:42,063 --> 00:20:44,355
The world don't give a fuck about me.

191
00:20:46,021 --> 00:20:50,021
- And I don't give a fuck about the world.
- So you have no allegiances?

192
00:20:50,105 --> 00:20:52,563
There are no lines
that you will not cross?

193
00:20:52,646 --> 00:20:55,146
You got lucky finding me. Yeah.

194
00:21:03,063 --> 00:21:04,063
Good.

195
00:21:04,813 --> 00:21:05,813
Well…

196
00:21:07,063 --> 00:21:09,771
Tonight, when the bombs fall,
you'll have to prove it.

197
00:21:28,355 --> 00:21:29,646
Johnny?

198
00:22:20,688 --> 00:22:25,771
<i>"I hurt my brothers,</i>
<i>mostly Arthur, the beast on chain."</i>

199
00:22:34,771 --> 00:22:36,480
No one comes to my house.

200
00:22:37,355 --> 00:22:42,396
Hey. I just opened the windows
to let some of the spirits out.

201
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:48,021
I'm here to give a message
for the <i>Rom Baro</i>.

202
00:22:48,896 --> 00:22:50,688
I'm told you are writing something.

203
00:22:51,438 --> 00:22:52,563
No, fuck…

204
00:23:07,105 --> 00:23:08,480
You think you know me.

205
00:23:12,730 --> 00:23:15,271
It's my twin sister's face
you see in mine.

206
00:23:18,521 --> 00:23:20,730
Even though she died some time ago,

207
00:23:22,021 --> 00:23:23,563
I still speak to her.

208
00:23:24,896 --> 00:23:26,355
In dreams.

209
00:23:27,688 --> 00:23:29,396
In séance.

210
00:23:32,105 --> 00:23:34,855
She wanted me to give you a message.

211
00:23:40,396 --> 00:23:41,896
You are easy to get around.

212
00:23:43,521 --> 00:23:45,230
Just like your house,

213
00:23:45,313 --> 00:23:49,313
you're easy to break into
if you have the right key.

214
00:23:50,438 --> 00:23:51,855
Your sister's name…

215
00:23:53,521 --> 00:23:54,521
was Zelda?

216
00:23:55,730 --> 00:23:58,188
Yes. I'm Kaulo Chiriklo.

217
00:23:58,688 --> 00:24:01,230
- In Romanes, it means…
- Blackbird.

218
00:24:03,646 --> 00:24:04,688
{\an8}That will help.

219
00:24:05,771 --> 00:24:07,021
So you, um…

220
00:24:08,813 --> 00:24:10,521
You slept with my sister.

221
00:24:11,188 --> 00:24:14,355
Stow Gypsy Fair, 1914.

222
00:24:14,438 --> 00:24:16,813
She had your baby, Duke.

223
00:24:17,980 --> 00:24:22,021
I know all about the baby
and the man he has become.

224
00:24:22,730 --> 00:24:23,980
I left him my kingdom.

225
00:24:24,063 --> 00:24:26,855
No, you abandoned your kingdom,
and you abandoned your son.

226
00:24:27,563 --> 00:24:28,688
He wasn't ready for it.

227
00:24:28,771 --> 00:24:33,355
If it's money he wants,
I gave him enough. Hear me?

228
00:24:34,480 --> 00:24:38,021
If it's trouble he's in,
I've trouble enough of me own.

229
00:24:38,105 --> 00:24:39,855
I know about your trouble, Mr. Shelby.

230
00:24:39,938 --> 00:24:42,980
I don't think you're going to
be able to write your way out of it.

231
00:24:43,063 --> 00:24:46,855
You live in a house haunted with ghosts.

232
00:24:47,521 --> 00:24:50,271
Of people who died 'cause of you.

233
00:24:54,021 --> 00:24:55,896
You still haven't given me your message.

234
00:24:58,855 --> 00:24:59,855
Huh.

235
00:25:02,813 --> 00:25:04,271
Your son is in trouble.

236
00:25:05,730 --> 00:25:07,313
He's working with evil men.

237
00:25:07,396 --> 00:25:10,938
Men who would destroy our people.
Gypsy people.

238
00:25:11,021 --> 00:25:13,063
I do not engage
in that kind of work anymore.

239
00:25:13,146 --> 00:25:16,646
If you agree
to come back and save your son,

240
00:25:16,730 --> 00:25:20,521
my sister and I will help you find peace.

241
00:25:23,355 --> 00:25:25,271
I saw the doors and windows open.

242
00:25:26,438 --> 00:25:27,855
What the fuck?

243
00:25:27,938 --> 00:25:29,855
Don't shoot, Mr. Dogs.

244
00:25:29,938 --> 00:25:34,271
I think down the Lee bloodline
we are, what, second cousins?

245
00:25:34,355 --> 00:25:37,980
Johnny, why don't you cook
those two pigeons you shot today?

246
00:25:40,271 --> 00:25:41,771
We have a guest.

247
00:25:42,396 --> 00:25:43,730
We have a what?

248
00:25:47,021 --> 00:25:50,105
That woman is
the queen of the Palmer Gypsies.

249
